name: The Navel of The World
description: The symbolism of the navel is linked to the idea of center. Several cultures spoke interchangeably of "center of the world" or "navel of the world". For the Incas, the center was in the city of Cuzco, for the Greeks it was in Delphi, where they placed a sacred stone that marked it, thus establishing the Omphalos or navel as a physical representation of the center of the world.
